Browning with us today.

00:02:05.730 --> 00:02:08.669
Nicole lost her beautiful and
talented daughter, Dominique,

00:02:08.669 --> 00:02:11.340
to suicide in 2007,
and has made it

00:02:11.340 --> 00:02:15.400
her mission to destigmatize
suicide and mental illness.

00:02:15.400 --> 00:02:17.640
I've known Nicole
since 2005 when

00:02:17.640 --> 00:02:21.900
I joined Viacom, which was
MTV Networks at the time.

00:02:21.900 --> 00:02:24.300
Nicole led a team
of over 100 people

00:02:24.300 --> 00:02:26.160
and was our fearless leader.

00:02:26.160 --> 00:02:28.560
In the span of my
career, I've come

00:02:28.560 --> 00:02:31.935
across a few truly genuine
and inspirational leaders,

00:02:31.935 --> 00:02:34.810
and Nicole is
absolutely one of them.

00:02:34.810 --> 00:02:36.450
She's a very special
woman and I'm

00:02:36.450 --> 00:02:39.930
so grateful that she agreed
to speak to us today.

00:02:39.930 --> 00:02:42.930
Nicole was a 21-year veteran
at Viacom, earning her way

00:02:42.930 --> 00:02:44.820
to President of
Content Distribution

00:02:44.820 --> 00:02:47.430
and Partner Marketing in 2000.

00:02:47.430 --> 00:02:49.650
While there, she
increased revenue 10 times

00:02:49.650 --> 00:02:54.630
to over $2 billion annually,
establishing her division

00:02:54.630 --> 00:02:57.240
as the company's second
largest revenue producer

00:02:57.240 --> 00:03:00.690
and building a portfolio
of over 20 valuable TV

00:03:00.690 --> 00:03:05.460
networks including Nickelodeon,
MTV, Comedy Central, and VH1.

00:03:05.460 --> 00:03:08.550
Prior to joining Viacom, Nicole
held various management, sales,

00:03:08.550 --> 00:03:11.490
and marketing positions at
Rainbow Media, the Weather

00:03:11.490 --> 00:03:14.310
Channel, Union
Carbide, and Xerox.

00:03:14.310 --> 00:03:17.250
In 2007, after
leaving Viacom Nicole

00:03:17.250 --> 00:03:21.180
founded her consulting firm,
Browning Media Consulting,

00:03:21.180 --> 00:03:25.110
which includes such clients
